  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He walked in the ways of his father (Jeroboam) and in his sin, i.e., in the calf-worship introduced by Jeroboam (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 12:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). When Nadab in the second year of his reign besieged Gibbethon, which the Philistines and occupied, Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house, I the family or tribe, of Issachar, conspired against him and slew him, and after he became king exterminated the whole house of Jeroboam, without leaving a single soul, whereby the prediction of the prophet Ahijah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) was fulfilled. Gibbethon, which was allotted to the Danites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), has not yet been discovered. It probably stood close to the Philistian border, and was taken by the Philistines, from whom the Israelites attempted to wrest it by siege under both Nadab and Baasha (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 16:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), though apparently without success. לא השׁאיר כּל־נשׁמה as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
